ProgressiveParts is a generator of multi-level copies of parts for KSP with Kerbalism integration.

This script scans the GameData folder of the specified KSP installation, finds all the parts
corresponding to the specified categories (probes, command modules, batteries, RTG, wheels,
thermal protection, lighting, parachutes), and creates progressive copies for them (Tier 1..Tier N).

Each category has its own list of technological nodes (from early to late).
The pressure and temperature for each copy are calculated by linear interpolation between
PRESSURE_MIN/PRESSURE_MAX and TEMP_MIN/TEMP_MAX depending on the position of the node in the progression.

Different performance modifiers are used for different types of parts.:
- Weight (all categories)
- Battery capacity
- Antenna range (antenna/comm)
- Speed and range of actuators (gearboards, robotics)
- Power and range of light (light)
- Aerodynamic drag and opening speed (parachute)

The output file (TieredPartsByCategory.cfg) contains blocks +PART[...], which, if
ModuleManager is available, will add copies of parts with the required characteristics to the game.
and by linking to the technology tree.

Usage:
python ProgressiveParts_1.0.py [path_cgamedata]
